social_posts.post_text: I’m so thankful for all of the amazing relationships I’ve had the opportunity to build this year. It’s been a year of growth, becoming more efficient, and just flat continuing to learn as much as I can. I’ve prayed so much for opportunities over the years. This year I have learned it’s not just about the opportunities,  but opportunities with the RIGHT people. I’m super excited to roll into 2023 with a more defined mindset to better serve everyone around me. God is GOOD, guys. None of us are perfect. But He is. In the coming year, do your best to love as Jesus loves. Everything else will fall right into place.

So excited to pass this home along to its new buyers! Praying it serves them so well as they grow there!

2022 has been such an amazing year! I’ve met some amazing people, had some great opportunities and learned so much. As I set goals for myself in 2023, my focus has shifted dramatically to not just the opportunities themselves but the people within those opportunities. I want to make sure that the opportunities I’m involved in are including people that are equally yoked with serving God first and foremost, serving our community in a big way and together, making the biggest impact possible on those around us. Not every opportunity is the right opportunity. Saying no is just as important as saying yes because the wrong opportunities will steal your time away from the right opportunities. I need to be much better at prayerfully discerning where my time is best spent to serve the greatest number of people. 2023 will be the best year yet! God is GOOD!

#ServeGodServePeople #RealEstate #Serve #God #Family #Business

Who struggles with ANXIETY? 🙋🏼‍♂️🙋🏼‍♂️🙋🏼‍♂️ I think everyone does in some form. As a business owner, stress is amplified in so many ways. It not only pulls us away from God but what God has called us to do with our lives. It’s intended to distract us, confuse us and take us off the path that God has set for us. If not managed, it is a seed that can grow us into something completely different than what God has called us to be. I’ve found myself not posting as much, not putting myself out there as much which I think is the opposite of what God has called me to do. I’m often so inspired and passionate about the things I post in hopes that it will inspire and influence someone that reads it. I’ve really felt God moving me to a new place in my life and my career that will help me serve better, be more available for my family and my team and be less stressed which I’m super thankful for. If you’re struggling, talk to someone. Get other’s opinions that you really value. It’s likely they will approach situations from a different perspective in the moment than you will. A few weeks ago we lost a really good friend that was clearly struggling. No one knew what he was going through but I sure wish we did. Needing help is okay. God gave us relationships for a reason. Please reach out.

It’s been a super busy few weeks! Very thankful for where I feel like God is leading me in my personal life. This year I’m focusing on leveraging more, loving people better and truly putting my relationship with God first. It’s so easy to get busy and say “yes” to the wrong things that pull you away from the right things. When I try to do things on my own without God, I get stressed and things get messy. I feel like I have a lot to offer those around me in terms of faith, growing their businesses and serving new buyers and sellers. I can’t provide effectively when I try to do things on my own. God has to be at the forefront and I have to focus on His will for my life first which can only make me a better Christian, husband, father and business owner. In that order.

Since more people tend to see/read your posts on your birthday, let me give God all the glory for a minute 🙌🏼 Over the last few months, I’ve made a point to only listen to worship music. I’m also an avid crime documentary junky… No idea why. I love that stuff. Cutting out things that don’t feed my spirit though has made the biggest difference in my life though. I can’t remember ever changing anything that has benefited me more. I’ve constantly struggled with stress and anxiety. I’m extremely hard on myself. Taking an account of the things I’ve allowed to enter my life has helped me refocus on God and what He has for my life. The stress and anxiety has dramatically reduced and I can only credit God. His word is so freeing. It’s literally the light that our souls need. Huge thank you to everyone that has taken the time to wish me a happy birthday today! I am so blessed with so many amazing people around me! 🙌🏼

Something that a lot of people don’t know about our business is how much push back we have gotten giving God all the glory for the success we’ve had. While we have also received a ton of support, there have been plenty of times where #ServeGodServePeople unfortunately has not been seen in a positive light. Almost always from other agents or people within the industry, fortunately never from a client. 

I never thought it would be viewed negatively. That’s kind of shocking to me, although it shouldn’t be surprising in our world today. The whole reason I got into business was to build something that represented God well and served people in a big way. 

It was amazing being in a room full of people where I could truly be open and share my heart on the subject at the Faithful Agent Conference this past week. To be on stage with such an amazing group of Christian leaders, there was a clear message sent that we simply strive to love God and love people through our businesses. Never to push a relationship with God on others, but just to love them in a way they may never have been loved before with the highest moral and value standards that God calls us to, regardless of their backgrounds. 

The Faithful Agent Conference was the peace that I’ve needed for a long time. To know that I’m not alone in my struggles was simply the best.

Running a business is fun (most of the time). There are times when you can imagine yourself doing anything else. God has me right where I’m supposed be, ect. 

Other days, the stress and anxiety are REAL. I’m extremely guilty of allowing other’s opinions of me affect me to a point of almost a depression. Carrying the weight of other families relying on all that we’re building can be heavy.

But God…

Every single day is a struggle between good and evil. And the devil is extremely good at using good things to manipulate your mind and throw you off course.

So what do we do? God’s word calls us to focus on all that is right, true, pure and honorable. (Philippians 4:8) Like everything else, we train our hearts and minds to focus on what God calls us to. That means shutting out all that is not that. 

We are also called to not be anxious about anything. But to enter every situation in prayer. To give all that we are to God. We serve the most caring and loving God. Which means he cares about even the smallest of situations in our lives.

We have SO much to be thankful for. Don’t let your blessings be shadowed by untruths and uncertainties. Train your mind to be fixed on the good.

What. A. Year 🙌🏼 So many times in my life I feel like I’m not doing enough to move the needle and achieve my goals. Looking back, this was a hugeeee year of growth for me in so many ways. 

In 2024, I need to do a much better job of relying on God to lead the way. I think it’s super easy to say that we trust God with our futures, but do we really act on it? This last quarter of 2023, I feel like I have done a better job of that.

2024 will be our best year yet. I’m so excited for all that God is building. My prayer is that everything we put our hands to has favor and blessing. That the world would see God through our work. And that we continue to really trust God in what he’s doing. 

If you ever pray for me at all, please pray these things over me. Thank you to everyone that has followed along this year! I love you guys!
